        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1985-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1985-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <head>234. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_RR_1">Reagan</persName> to
                    Yugoslav President <persName corresp="#p_VR_1">Vlajkovic</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d234fn1">Source: Reagan Library, <persName corresp="#p_DP_1">Paula J. Dobriansky</persName> Files, Yugoslavia (10).
                        No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1985-10-31">October 31, 1985</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. President:</salute>
                </opener>
                <!--<pb facs="d234-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d234-2"/>-->
                <p>I have learned that through an unfortunate and inadvertent administrative error,
                    you did not receive my invitation to the reception I hosted for heads of State
                    in New York on October 23. I regret any difficulty that this may have caused
                    you. <rs corresp="recW6DpFu8d7ioWcO" type="compound-subject">Relations</rs> with
                    Yugoslavia are very important to the United States, and I had very much looked
                    forward to meeting you in New York.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RR_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ronald Reagan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
